abstract: Senator Marco Rubio avoided making a determination as to whether the president’s conduct was appropriate.
snippet: Senator Marco Rubio avoided making a determination as to whether the president’s conduct was appropriate.
lead_paragraph: As Republican senators announced they would vote to acquit President Trump, they cited a reason divorced from the merits of the president’s conduct, arguing that removing Mr. Trump months away from the presidential election would serve only to deepen the nation’s bitter divisions.

abstract: The millennial former mayor of a midsize city has far surpassed expectations in the 2020 race. He doesn’t get fired up. Can he fire up people in Iowa?
snippet: The millennial former mayor of a midsize city has far surpassed expectations in the 2020 race. He doesn’t get fired up. Can he fire up people in Iowa?
lead_paragraph: OTTUMWA, Iowa — No presidential campaign is spared its awkward moments: overlong hugs from supporters, groaners about the Iowa weather, white lies about the caliber of the local cuisine.

abstract: Unexpectedly bad data leaves Europe with little margin for error as Brexit takes effect and the coronavirus looms.
snippet: Unexpectedly bad data leaves Europe with little margin for error as Brexit takes effect and the coronavirus looms.
lead_paragraph: Friday was not a good day for Europe. As the European Union officially became smaller, losing Britain as a member, new data showed that economic growth in the bloc came almost to a standstill and that it is in danger of slipping into recession.

abstract: Coverage about John R. Bolton’s unpublished book was evidence of the need to call the former aide as a witness, the lawmaker said.
snippet: Coverage about John R. Bolton’s unpublished book was evidence of the need to call the former aide as a witness, the lawmaker said.
lead_paragraph: Representative Adam B. Schiff of California, the lead Democratic House manager, opened by referring to The New York Times’s revelation on Friday that President Trump’s role in the Ukraine pressure campaign began earlier than previously known. Mr. Schiff emphasized that Pat A. Cipollone, the White House counsel, was present when the president delivered that instruction.
headline_main: Citing reporting by The Times, Schiff starts a final push for witnesses.
byline_original: By Patricia Mazzei and Michael D. Shear

abstract: Multiple events in the coming week are likely to give the president a window to declare vindication in an inquiry he has repeatedly declared a “hoax” or a “sham.”
snippet: Multiple events in the coming week are likely to give the president a window to declare vindication in an inquiry he has repeatedly declared a “hoax” or a “sham.”
lead_paragraph: If the Senate acquits President Trump in the next 24 hours, it will be a political gift for him that couldn’t come at a better time.

abstract: “Lamar speaks for lots and lots of us,” Senator Ben Sasse said. He did not elaborate.
snippet: “Lamar speaks for lots and lots of us,” Senator Ben Sasse said. He did not elaborate.
lead_paragraph: Senator Ben Sasse, Republican of Nebraska, has said little during the impeachment trial. And he told reporters briefly on Friday that he would remain silent. But he did offer one comment about Senator Lamar Alexander, Republican of Tennessee, who said late Thursday that President Trump’s actions were not impeachable.

abstract: Deputies and Secret Service agents fired on the woman’s  S.U.V., which was moving more than 70 miles per hour as it neared President Trump’s resort, the authorities said.
snippet: Deputies and Secret Service agents fired on the woman’s  S.U.V., which was moving more than 70 miles per hour as it neared President Trump’s resort, the authorities said.
lead_paragraph: An opera singer who the authorities say acted irrationally, danced on the top of an S.U.V. and led officers on a chase was fired at by sheriff’s deputies and Secret Service agents on Friday after her vehicle breached two security checkpoints at Mar-a-Lago, President Trump’s resort in Palm Beach, Fla.

abstract: Her vote means that Republicans have the support they need to block witnesses and bring the trial to a swift conclusion.
snippet: Her vote means that Republicans have the support they need to block witnesses and bring the trial to a swift conclusion.
lead_paragraph: Senator Lisa Murkowski, Republican of Alaska, said Friday she would vote against including new witnesses and documents in President Trump’s impeachment trial, likely dealing a fatal blow to Democrats’ attempts to compel new evidence as she lamented that “Congress has failed.”

abstract: Leaders are divided over a global solution to taxing Silicon Valley giants, a fight for big tax dollars that threatens to disrupt global trade.
snippet: Leaders are divided over a global solution to taxing Silicon Valley giants, a fight for big tax dollars that threatens to disrupt global trade.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — The Trump administration and leaders of other wealthy nations remain at odds over how to tax technology companies and other businesses that operate online, negotiators confirmed on Friday, an impasse that threatens to inflame global trade tensions if not resolved by year’s end.
